  "description": {
    "en": "A stout, low-slung mammal known for its digging abilities and distinctive facial stripes.",
    "zh": "一种粗壮低矮的哺乳动物，以其挖掘能力和独特的面部条纹而闻名。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "American badgers have flat, wedge-shaped bodies built close to the ground, weighing 6 to 12 kilograms. They have short, powerful legs with long front claws that can be up to 5 centimeters long, perfect for digging. Their face has a striking black and white pattern with a white stripe running from their nose over the top of their head.",
      "zh": "美洲獾有扁平的楔形身体，紧贴地面，体重6到12公斤。它们有短而有力的腿，前爪可长达5厘米，非常适合挖掘。它们的面部有醒目的黑白花纹，一条白色条纹从鼻子延伸到头顶。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "American badgers are expert diggers that hunt ground squirrels, prairie dogs, and other burrowing animals by digging them out of their tunnels at amazing speed. They sometimes team up with coyotes to hunt together, where the coyote chases prey above ground while the badger digs below. They are mostly active at night and are known for being tough and fearless when cornered.",
      "zh": "美洲獾是挖掘高手，它们以惊人的速度将地松鼠、土拨鼠和其他穴居动物从洞穴中挖出来捕食。它们有时会和郊狼合作狩猎，郊狼在地面上追赶猎物，而獾在地下挖掘。它们主要在夜间活动，被逼到角落时以强悍无畏著称。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "American badgers live in dry, open grasslands, prairies, and farmlands across western and central North America. They range from south-central Canada through the western United States to central Mexico. They prefer areas with loose, sandy soil that is easy to dig through.",
      "zh": "美洲獾生活在北美洲西部和中部干燥开阔的草原、大草原和农田中。它们的分布范围从加拿大中南部到美国西部，一直延伸到墨西哥中部。它们喜欢松软的沙质土壤，便于挖掘。"
    }
  },
